uk.co.strangeskies.collection.stream

Class ResourceStream<T,S extends java.util.stream.BaseStream<T,S>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.collection.stream.ResourceStream<T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements of the stream
    S - the type of the stream
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.util.stream.BaseStream<T,S>, BaseStreamDecorator<T,S>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ResourceStream.DoubleResourceStream, ResourceStream.IntResourceStream, ResourceStream.LongResourceStream, ResourceStream.ReferenceResourceStream

    public abstract class ResourceStream<T,S extends java.util.stream.BaseStream<T,S>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BaseStreamDecorator<T,S>
    A stream decorator over some sort of resource which only opens the resource upon invocation of a terminal operation, and then guarantees resource closure when the operation is complete.
